    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Is Alcohol the Culprit in Violence?</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Dr Gabor Somjen letter on Caroline Knapp's June 21 article on alcohol and violence deplores terrible social and health consequences of drinking</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Caroline Knapp's June 21 Op-Ed article finally addresses one of the main problems facing our society today. As much as smoking or even  secondhand smoking is bad for your health, it does not compare with the terrible health and social consequences that alcohol creates in our society. Where is the social outrage, and when is Congress going to do something about the problem?</p>
        <p>GABOR SOMJEN, M.D.  Dover, N.J., June 21, 2000</p>
      </block>
